			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="/images/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				  The best placve(that I know of) for tailoring materials, patterns, and prices is in Halas(the barbarian city). It has everyting you need to get started. ITs large sewing kit goes for 1 plat(just ask someone to lend you a plat and offer to make them a full set of patchwork armor in return). The ruined bear pelts go for around 1s, and we also have cat and wolf pelts. You don't have to travel to town to buy most of your patterns. If your a barbarian and you make a helm then it will the coolest thing you'll ever see! its a bear head helm! when you're attack and you slash an enemy then you can see the teeth show(SWEET!). Also, in halos, many people will sell you the armor for cheap! I got a full set of patchwork armor for 5gg. Its kind of funny to imagine a giant person like a barbarian with a ball of thread and a needle quilting a Gorget. hehe. <BR>
<BR>
        Sanamer Barbarian Warrior
