	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="/images/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am a lvl 88 tailor. In my experience as a human monk, the best way to go about tailoring at lower levels is to go to Northern Desert of Ro. The first as you are leaving E.Freeport has large sewing kits and plenty of patterns. The patterns that you don't find there are in E. Freeport in the Leather and Hide. After you buy your sewing kit and patterns go into e. commons. Kill every wolf, black bear, and spiderling you see. Two spiderling silk can be combined to make silk thread. two silk thread make a bandage(used for bind wound skill). These become trivial at 15. Also in e. commons if you are a higher level go after pumas. Do this until patchwork becomes trivial at 26. Then you need to kill large and giant spiders to get spider silk. Combine two spider silk to make silk swatches. silk swatches are used for making raw silk, which becomes trivial at 37. I hope you hung on to all of those medium quality pelts you got from pumas because at 37 you start making studded. YOu need m. quality pelts and studs made by a blacksmith. That should be enough to get you to 50. At 50 start making cured silk. It costs the same to make as studded but sells for a large profit. A full set of cured silk will sell for 85-100pp. Also you should go to Highpass and get your brewing up to lvl 46 at which Heady Kiolas become trivial. If you have any questions on any of these tips e-mail me at:glenncw@yahoo.com<BR>
<BR>
Zenloch &lt;Sacred Legions&gt;<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

